Please describe in detail a time in which you felt guilty over something that happened between you and another person.

Please describe in detail a time when you felt disrespected by someone else. Perhaps you felt like you were treated with less courtesy than others, or you were slighted by someone, for example.

 

Please, indicate where and when this happened and provide the initials of the person(s) who treated you that way, if possible.

cond_guilt: I forgot the present for a friend's birthday.

I'm guilty at how I used to talk to my friend BS. Our relationship was rocky for years because I was too often sarcastic, or would make disparaging comments about them (in jest, but obviously hurtful in hindsight). They are one of my best friends now, but I feel guilty that I caused them any harm.

cond_disr: a few months ago I visited a college friend, A.P., in berkeley, ca. we were planning on going to a protest (with masks), then I was going to stay the night and the next day we were going to go on a hike. but after the protest, A.P. decided he wanted to go to a party indoors. this was not the plan, and also unsafe because of corona. i expressed discomfort but he decided to stay, so i ended up leaving before the party, not spending the night, and not hiking with him. the next day he apologized but i still am upset about it
